<taxonomicName authorityName="Fang &amp; Nan &amp; Feng &amp; Lv &amp; Liu &amp; Liu &amp; Xie" authorityYear="2021" box="[136,394,244,271]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Batrachospermaceae" genus="Kumanoa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nemaliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="baiyunensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,394,244,271]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">Kumanoa baiyunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
K.-P.Fang, F.-R.Nan &amp; S.-L.Xie 
<emphasis box="[768,853,245,270]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">sp. nov.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[867,997,244,270]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,245,1731,1757]" captionTargetBox="[194,1395,189,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[183,1405,184,1710]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Morphological structures of Kumanoa baiyunensis sp. nov. A. Habitat in the stony pool of Baiyun Mountain. Small thallus of K. baiyunensis (white arrow). B. Vegetative thalli of K. baiyunensis.. C. Upper part of thallus with abundant branches, containing spherical carposporophytes (arrows). D. Main axis with confluent whorls containing spherical and sessile carposporophytes, one per whorl (arrows). E. Mature main axis with distinct barrelshaped whorls. F. Node showing axial cell (arrow). G. Cortical filament cells (arrow). H. Densely packed cells of spherical carposporophyte. I. Spherical, sparse, and single-grown spermatangia (arrows), terminal on primary fascicles. J. Young carposporophyte with obovoid carposporangia (arrows) at the tips of gonimoblast filaments. K. Carpogonium with club-shaped trichogyne (arrow) on a helically twisted carpogonial branch (arrowhead). L. Fertilized carpogonium with club-shaped and distinctly stalked (arrowhead) trichogyne (arrow), and gonimoblast initials (double arrow). Scale bars: 5 mm (B), 100 μm (C &amp; D), 50 μm (E), 20 μm (F–L)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5572022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5572022/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">Figs. 3A–L</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="95" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,316,1099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,274,316,342]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">Description</emphasis>
:—Plants monoecious, moderately mucilaginous, dark green, small, only 
<quantity box="[1082,1184,316,343]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1 cm</quantity>
high. Thallus branching irregular, frequent in the upper part of the thallus. Whorls well developed, confluent, barrel-shaped, 350–450 µm wide. Internodes 150–350 µm; axis colorless, axial cells 20–50 µm in diameter; cortical filaments profuse, cylindrical, 5–10 um in diameter, 20 µm or more long. Primary fascicles straight, dichotomously branched, 2-3 times branched, composed of 5–7 cells, ellipsoidal, 5–8 µm in diameter, 20–40 µm long. Secondary fascicles, abundant, covering the entire internode, unbranched or dichotomously branched, shorter or as long as the primary fascicles, composed of 3–7 cells. Spermatangia spherical, sparse, single-grown, terminal on primary fascicles, 7–9 µm in diameter. Carpogonial branches helically twisted, arising from the pericentral cells; involucral filaments short, dense, composed of 1–3 cells; carpogonia with club-shaped trichogynes, distinctly stalked, 30–50 µm long, 6–10 µm in diameter. Carposporophytes sessile, one per whorl, lower or as high as whorl radius, dense and spherical, 150–250 µm in diameter. Carposporangia obovoid or elliptical, 7–10 µm in diameter, 15–20 µm long, terminal on gonimoblast filaments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,316,1099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,314,712,738]" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
―The new species differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[750,949,712,738]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Batrachospermaceae" genus="Kumanoa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nemaliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="95" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[750,859,713,738]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">Kumanoa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the following combination of characters: small plant size with abundant branching in upper part of thallus; carposporophytes spherical and one per whorl; club-shaped trichogynes with distinct stalk; spermatangia sparse and single-grown, terminal on primary fascicles. Diagnostic DNA sequence: 
<emphasis box="[446,483,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">rbc</emphasis>
L, COI-5P and LSU (accession number: 
<accessionNumber box="[936,1071,820,846]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MW798266" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">MW798266</accessionNumber>
for 
<emphasis box="[1117,1154,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">rbc</emphasis>
L, 
<accessionNumber box="[1184,1320,820,846]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MW798267" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">MW798267</accessionNumber>
for COI-5P and 
<accessionNumber box="[183,319,856,882]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MW794124" pageId="6" pageNumber="95">MW794124</accessionNumber>
for UPA).
</paragraph>
